  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "PROJECT DIRECTOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Manage and direct projects, ensuring delivery within approved scope, schedule, budget, and quality requirements.</li><li>Guide and support project manager in day-to-day execution, providing clear direction on priorities, decision-making, and issue resolution.</li><li>Develop realistic project plans, schedules, and delivery strategies aligned with business objectives and operational constraints.</li><li>Coordinate with senior management, clients, subcontractors, internal teams, and the Korean head office through regular reporting and meetings to ensure alignment and timely decision-making.</li><li>Monitor project risks, issues, and changes, and implement practical mitigation and change control actions as required.</li><li>Ensure compliance with contract terms, regulatory standards, and internal procedures throughout project execution.</li><li>Track project performance, including cost control, resource allocation, and progress against key milestones, and take corrective action when needed.</li><li>Establish and maintain consistent project management processes, tools, and reporting standards.</li><li>Provide coaching, feedback, and on-the-job support to project team members to improve performance and delivery capability.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Civil & Structural Engineering recognized by PE Board or qualification acceptable to the Commissioner of Building Control as eligible for application as a Resident Engineer.</li><li>Minimum 15 years of hands-on experience in civil infrastructure projects such as roads, bridges, railways, metro systems, and tunnels. </li><li>At least 10 years’ experience in managing design and construction teams.</li><li>Fluent in both Korean and English, with the ability to communicate effectively in a professional project environment.</li></ul>",
